WEBVTT

00:01.120 --> 00:04.499
Previously on "Stumptown"...
Hoffman: I just can't tell
if she's playing games.

00:04.500 --> 00:05.956
The P.I.?
Yeah.

00:05.960 --> 00:08.451
This may come as a shock,
but some women --

00:08.460 --> 00:10.496
you got to let 'em know
how you feel.

00:10.500 --> 00:12.491
Mira.
Que pasa?

00:12.500 --> 00:14.877
That's a lot of va-voom
for book club, huh?

00:14.880 --> 00:17.201
It was
the only thing clean.

00:17.210 --> 00:18.700
Michael: Is that what you
came here to tell me?

00:18.710 --> 00:21.076
I -- I was a bad father?
You never
reached out to me.

00:21.080 --> 00:22.741
You told me you never wanted
to see me again, you --

00:22.750 --> 00:23.819
It was 20 years ago.

00:23.830 --> 00:25.661
You were the dad.
You could've fixed it.

00:25.670 --> 00:26.910
There was an investigation

00:26.920 --> 00:29.161
into the IED explosion
that killed Benny.

00:29.170 --> 00:30.569
There's more
to this story.

00:30.580 --> 00:31.740
A lot more.

00:33.580 --> 00:35.241
[ Rock music plays
inside club ]

00:35.250 --> 00:37.536
Bouncer: Okay.
Very clever.

00:37.540 --> 00:39.747
The lighter-on-the-license trick
never works.

00:39.750 --> 00:42.617
Trick? No.

00:42.620 --> 00:44.576
No, actually,
it's a really funny story --

00:44.580 --> 00:46.161
Nice try.
Give me that back.

00:46.170 --> 00:47.239
I'm gonna have to
confiscate it.

00:47.250 --> 00:48.569
Hey.
I just need to get the --

00:48.580 --> 00:49.615
Stop it!

00:49.620 --> 00:50.951
Ohh.

00:50.960 --> 00:53.281
Oh, that's nice.
That's real nice.

00:53.290 --> 00:57.112
[ Music continues ]

00:57.120 --> 00:58.747
A little sloppy
on the dismount.

00:58.750 --> 01:00.240
[ Sighs ]

01:04.330 --> 01:05.740
Ugh.

01:05.750 --> 01:07.820
[ Sighs ]

01:07.830 --> 01:10.537
Don't think I'm easy just 'cause
you found me in the gutter.

01:10.540 --> 01:12.667
[ Chuckles ] I've, uh,
seen you around campus.

01:12.670 --> 01:14.319
You okay?
No.

01:14.330 --> 01:16.491
I really wanted to
see this show.

01:16.500 --> 01:18.957
Oh. Yeah?

01:18.960 --> 01:21.872
[ Door creaks ]

01:21.880 --> 01:23.199
[ Music continues in distance,
door closes ]

01:23.210 --> 01:24.700
It's a nice view.

01:24.710 --> 01:25.995
It's not the view.

01:26.000 --> 01:28.036
Stand here.

01:28.040 --> 01:29.917
Okay.

01:29.920 --> 01:31.376
[Tegan and Sara's "Walking
With a Ghost" plays faintly ]

01:31.380 --> 01:34.827
I said please,
please don't insist

01:34.830 --> 01:36.741
[ Music grows louder ]

01:36.750 --> 01:40.493
I was walking
with a ghost
[ Chuckles ] Wow.

01:40.500 --> 01:43.162
Why does it sound like
we're right near the stage?

01:43.170 --> 01:44.205
Something
about the acoustics.

01:44.210 --> 01:45.370
Brick hits metal
just right, and --

01:45.380 --> 01:47.496
It's amazing.
Thank you.

01:47.500 --> 01:48.990
[ Laughs ]

01:49.000 --> 01:50.615
No matter which way you stay

01:50.620 --> 01:52.576
Benjamin.

01:52.580 --> 01:53.820
Blackbird.

01:53.830 --> 01:55.570
Call me Benny.

01:59.750 --> 02:02.913
I was walking with a ghost

02:02.920 --> 02:06.492
I said please,
please don't insist

02:08.500 --> 02:10.570
I was walking
with a ghost

02:10.580 --> 02:13.663
I said please,
please don't insist

02:13.670 --> 02:16.070
Major Elders,
this is my friend, Dex Parios.

02:16.080 --> 02:18.378
Pleasure.
Thanks for coming
all this way, Major.

02:18.380 --> 02:20.450
I have family
in the area,

02:20.460 --> 02:22.746
so it was a good excuse.

02:22.750 --> 02:27.119
Besides,
saying I owe my life to Jeremy

02:27.120 --> 02:28.997
is no exaggeration.

02:29.000 --> 02:30.911
Out of my mind

02:30.920 --> 02:32.205
Uh, so you have information

02:32.210 --> 02:35.373
about the IED
that killed Benjamin Blackbird?

02:35.380 --> 02:37.746
You understand the file
is classified, Top Secret.

02:37.750 --> 02:39.536
Dex is one of us,
Major.

02:39.540 --> 02:40.871
Out of my mind

02:40.880 --> 02:42.245
[ Sighs ]

02:42.250 --> 02:44.536
Out of my mind, out of my...

02:44.540 --> 02:47.498
You were told the explosives
were stolen by the Taliban,

02:47.500 --> 02:49.877
specifically by someone
you had in custody?

02:49.880 --> 02:51.108
Yes, sir.

02:51.120 --> 02:53.452
Well, you were
wrongfully informed.

02:53.460 --> 02:55.746
Now, Jeremy told me
what you've been through

02:55.750 --> 02:57.786
and that you blame yourself
for the attack.

02:57.790 --> 02:59.917
I'm sorry. Um...

02:59.920 --> 03:01.285
Out of my mind

03:01.290 --> 03:04.202
Wrong--
Wrongfully informed?

03:04.210 --> 03:06.371
The bomb signature
on the IED

03:06.380 --> 03:09.281
matched a wildcat
assassmation team

03:09.290 --> 03:10.917
associated
with the Haqqanis.

03:10.920 --> 03:12.239
Now, they're
a northern tribe --

03:12.250 --> 03:15.242
-No connection to the Taliban.
-Exactly.

03:15.250 --> 03:17.377
We believe that
Private Blackbird's Humvee

03:17.380 --> 03:19.371
was targeted erroneously.

03:19.380 --> 03:21.701
You see? There was nothing
you could have done.

03:21.710 --> 03:23.917
The -- The -- The Haqqanis

03:25.920 --> 03:27.285
Their fight is in Kandahar.

03:30.790 --> 03:32.610
I'd like to see the file.

03:34.920 --> 03:38.242
Well, I-I feel like I've said
more than I should already.

03:38.250 --> 03:39.820
Dex, the Major's
taking a real risk

03:39.830 --> 03:41.570
trying to
get you some closure.

03:41.580 --> 03:44.413
I understand that, but
none of this makes any sense.

03:44.420 --> 03:46.706
If Benny was targeted
erroneously,

03:46.710 --> 03:48.371
why is it classified
Top Secret?

03:48.380 --> 03:50.325
You were in
Intelligence.

03:50.330 --> 03:52.116
You know that
classifications can be set

03:52.120 --> 03:53.610
for any number
of reasons.

03:53.620 --> 03:55.497
You know,
I think I should be going.

03:55.500 --> 03:57.036
Of course. Thank you.
Thanks.
N-N-No.
They're covering it up.

03:57.040 --> 03:58.530
Dex --
No.

03:58.540 --> 04:00.531
What -- What --
What really happened, Major?

04:00.540 --> 04:01.529
Tell me.

04:03.040 --> 04:05.167
You got the information
you wanted.

04:05.170 --> 04:06.740
I didn't get
any information.

04:06.750 --> 04:07.910
-Sir.
-He didn't --

04:07.920 --> 04:09.490
[ Sighs ]
Good luck.

04:13.000 --> 04:14.319
Dex.
No.

04:16.830 --> 04:18.240
So hot

04:18.250 --> 04:20.241
Give it all that you got

04:20.250 --> 04:22.115
Give it all that you got

04:22.120 --> 04:24.281
Give it all that you got

04:24.290 --> 04:25.826
One love

04:25.830 --> 04:27.661
Give it all that you got
Hey! [ Chuckles]

04:27.670 --> 04:28.568
Woman: Hey!

04:28.580 --> 04:30.411
You have amazing legs.

04:30.420 --> 04:32.615
-Thank you.
-Oh, I'm sorry.

04:32.620 --> 04:34.576
My partner and I were sure
you were a unicorn.

04:34.580 --> 04:36.662
Oh. First timer.

04:36.670 --> 04:39.377
Come find us
when you're ready to play.

04:39.380 --> 04:40.916
Okay.
[ Chuckles ]

04:40.920 --> 04:43.070
...so give me some, baby

04:43.080 --> 04:44.616
I won't ever stop so

04:44.620 --> 04:47.874
Come here often?
[ Scoffs ]
I did my research.

04:47.880 --> 04:49.825
So, a unicorn is...?

04:49.830 --> 04:51.661
Single woman,
basically.

04:51.670 --> 04:53.570
The girl we're looking for
is a unicorn.

04:53.580 --> 04:56.663
Floating between couples
and older men no one wants.

04:56.670 --> 04:59.412
So, it's easier to drug
a desperate older man, huh?

04:59.420 --> 05:01.115
With deep pockets.

05:01.120 --> 05:02.530
Check out
the number of dudes

05:02.540 --> 05:04.531
sporting diamond watches
in this room.

05:04.540 --> 05:06.417
And our girl's
already made off with 200k.

05:06.420 --> 05:07.739
She's no dummy.

05:07.750 --> 05:09.115
It's got to get you thinking,
though.

05:09.120 --> 05:10.576
Like, what's really
behind this, right?

05:10.580 --> 05:12.320
Like, the...

05:12.330 --> 05:14.070
Does the marriage
just need spice,

05:14.080 --> 05:15.707
or are these people
looking for the exit, you know?

05:15.710 --> 05:17.325
No judgement.

05:17.330 --> 05:19.378
I'm a one guy
kind of girl.

05:19.380 --> 05:21.780
_ There's a whole lot
of judgement In that, actually,

05:21.790 --> 05:23.997
but, uh,
I feel the same.
[ Chuckles ]

05:24.000 --> 05:25.160
Maybe I drank too much or

05:25.170 --> 05:26.569
But, like,
the opposite, though.

05:26.580 --> 05:28.036
Yeah.

05:29.120 --> 05:30.496
I'm gonna make
another round.

05:30.500 --> 05:31.956
Hold on.

05:31.960 --> 05:34.417
I've seen this guy before.
With the man bun.

05:34.420 --> 05:36.741
From the other club
we sat on.

05:36.750 --> 05:39.378
Gir|_ seems
pretty Interested.

05:39.380 --> 05:40.608
She came in
with a dude in black.

05:40.620 --> 05:43.282
It looks like
they're recruiting a third.

05:43.290 --> 05:44.450
Oh.

05:44.460 --> 05:46.030
That's how it happens.

05:46.040 --> 05:49.328
I won't ever stop,
so give me some, baby

05:49.330 --> 05:50.911
Oh, no.

05:50.920 --> 05:52.820
Friend of yours?

05:52.830 --> 05:55.116
It's Tookie's wife.

05:55.120 --> 05:57.031
Give me some, baby

05:57.040 --> 05:57.745
I won't ever stop

05:57.750 --> 05:59.115
[ Laughs ]

05:59.120 --> 06:01.418
Benny's death was your fault,

06:01.420 --> 06:03.570
now it's not your fault,
but there's more to it.

06:03.580 --> 06:05.536
I'm sorry. I'm getting
a little bit of whiplash.

06:05.540 --> 06:06.950
Yeah, tell me about it.

06:06.960 --> 06:09.417
[ Sighs ]
I just want the truth.

06:09.420 --> 06:11.240
You think the truth
will bring you peace?

06:11.250 --> 06:14.879
I don't know. I don't know
if I know what peace feels like.

06:14.880 --> 06:16.780
Right.
Well, where you going?

06:16.790 --> 06:18.371
Hmm?
What do you mean?

06:18.380 --> 06:19.665
Well, the only time
you don't day-drink

06:19.670 --> 06:21.570
is when you got to drive
someplace far.

06:21.580 --> 06:22.877
Ah. Yeah.

06:22.880 --> 06:24.996
I'm, uh -- I'm going out
to Hood River.

06:25.000 --> 06:27.286
There's a guy who used to
be on Benny's unit.

06:27.290 --> 06:29.451
He lives out there.
Thomas Junes.

06:29.460 --> 06:31.701
After Sue Lynn
kicked me out of the funeral,

06:31.710 --> 06:33.416
TJ reached out.
Hmm.

06:33.420 --> 06:36.162
He made me feel like
I was part of Benny's life.

06:36.170 --> 06:38.491
I'm hoping maybe he can
shed some light on all this.

06:38.500 --> 06:40.616
And you?
What about me?

06:40.620 --> 06:43.418
You only day-drink when you got
something on your mind, so --

06:43.420 --> 06:44.739
[ Chuckling ]
I don't think that's true.

06:44.750 --> 06:47.287
It's 100% true.

06:47.290 --> 06:48.780
My dad messaged me.

06:48.790 --> 06:50.917
Oh. Wow.

06:50.920 --> 06:52.535
Yeah, so my dad's son,
I guess,

06:52.540 --> 06:55.327
has a baseball tournament
In Seattle,

06:55.330 --> 06:57.321
and my dad wants to come see me
on the way there.

06:57.330 --> 06:59.742
That's great.
Is it, though?

06:59.750 --> 07:02.287
I mean, 25 years, and
not so much as a birthday card,

07:02.290 --> 07:04.246
and all of a sudden,
he wants a relationship?

07:04.250 --> 07:06.457
Well, you said yourself
he's changed.

07:06.460 --> 07:07.916
That's hard to do.

07:07.920 --> 07:09.114
Maybe you should
give him a chance.

07:09.120 --> 07:10.747
Just weird, right?

07:10.750 --> 07:12.957
All this digging up
in the past.

07:12.960 --> 07:14.871
When do we get to
move forward?

07:17.460 --> 07:19.667
I'm gonna take off.
I'll see you later.

07:19.670 --> 07:22.616
Every sound
feels like a kiss

07:22.620 --> 07:24.451
Go on, then,
and don't look back

07:24.460 --> 07:26.416
[ Ratchet clicking ]

07:26.420 --> 07:27.705
[ Brakes screech ]

07:27.710 --> 07:29.416
TJ?

07:29.420 --> 07:32.457
I'll be damned.
Benny's girl.

07:32.460 --> 07:34.997
Can I talk to you
for a minute?

07:35.000 --> 07:36.410
[ Dog barks in distance ]

07:36.420 --> 07:39.241
Oh.
Haqqanis killed Benny?

07:39.250 --> 07:41.457
That's what I was told.

07:41.460 --> 07:42.609
I never heard anything
about that.

07:42.620 --> 07:43.666
Thanks.

07:43.670 --> 07:45.376
Yeah.

07:45.380 --> 07:47.280
Does that make
any sense to you?

07:47.290 --> 07:49.246
No.
It makes no sense.

07:49.250 --> 07:51.161
We were
a Civil Affairs Unit.

07:51.170 --> 07:54.287
I mean, your village
was plundered by the Taliban,

07:54.290 --> 07:55.951
we went in
with funds to rebuild.

07:55.960 --> 07:59.168
Of course, a lot of times,
we made things worse.

07:59.170 --> 08:00.285
You know, "He got more
than I did"

08:00.290 --> 08:02.201
or, "Someone stole
my share."

08:02.210 --> 08:05.111
Yeah. Winning hearts
and minds, huh?
Mm.

08:05.120 --> 08:07.953
I am actually ashamed
to say, but...

08:07.960 --> 08:11.168
I do my best not to think
about those days.

08:11.170 --> 08:12.706
When I do, I miss him.

08:14.620 --> 08:15.530
[ Sighs ]

08:15.540 --> 08:17.451
Yeah, me too.

08:20.000 --> 08:22.241
You are, uh,
quite the collector.

08:22.250 --> 08:24.411
[ Chuckles ]

08:24.420 --> 08:26.991
Is, um --
Is that from Afghanistan?

08:27.000 --> 08:28.376
Brought it home
from Kabul.

08:28.380 --> 08:29.995
Hmm.
Where'd you get it?

08:30.000 --> 08:31.991
Oh, I don't know.
Some bush market.

08:32.000 --> 08:33.877
It's high quality
for a bush market.

08:33.880 --> 08:35.370
Usually
cheap reproductions.

08:35.380 --> 08:37.245
Hey, I got lucky.

08:37.250 --> 08:39.878
Or you found it
in a bombed-out building

08:39.880 --> 08:41.575
about to be bulldozed.

08:41.580 --> 08:45.323
Better with you than buried
under rubble, I guess.

08:46.790 --> 08:50.419
Why does it feel like
a cold wind just blew in?

08:50.420 --> 08:52.069
Why does it feel like
you're holding out on me?

08:52.080 --> 08:53.616
I don't know anything.

08:53.620 --> 08:55.747
So, nobody questioned you
about the bombing?

08:55.750 --> 08:57.570
Nobody questioned me
about any bombing.

08:57.580 --> 08:59.161
Benny's death
is Top Secret.

08:59.170 --> 09:00.239
That doesn't seem strange
to you?

09:00.250 --> 09:02.491
Eh, strange or not,
I wasn't questioned.

09:02.500 --> 09:04.536
Okay, then who was?

09:04.540 --> 09:06.952
Dex...

09:06.960 --> 09:08.530
[ Sighs ]

09:08.540 --> 09:10.917
You can't
bring him back.

09:10.920 --> 09:12.569
So, you gotta stop asking

09:12.580 --> 09:14.377
questions you're never
gonna get answers to.

09:14.380 --> 09:16.280
What the hell
does that mean?

09:16.290 --> 09:18.372
It's a long drive
back to Portland.

09:18.380 --> 09:19.449
[ Bottle thuds ]

09:19.460 --> 09:21.166
I'm done talking
about the war.

09:27.710 --> 09:29.496
[ Door creaks ]

09:31.500 --> 09:34.378
[ Sighs ]

09:48.540 --> 09:51.077
[ Pearl Jam's "Daughter" plays ]

09:51.080 --> 09:53.492
Shh!
Parents are sleeping.

09:53.500 --> 09:56.162
_ You're a lifesaver. Machines
In my dorm are always broken.

09:56.170 --> 09:58.411
And they cost
two bucks a load.

09:58.420 --> 10:00.240
[ Chuckles ]

10:00.250 --> 10:02.115
I'm not afraid to meet
your parents, you know.

10:02.120 --> 10:03.496
I'm very charming.

10:03.500 --> 10:04.876
Yeah.

10:04.880 --> 10:06.745
They're probably gonna like you
more than they like me.

10:08.580 --> 10:11.993
Alone, listless

10:12.000 --> 10:14.321
Well, what about your brother?
When can I meet him?

10:14.330 --> 10:15.706
Soon.

10:15.710 --> 10:18.281
And he's excited
to meet you.
Yeah?

10:18.290 --> 10:20.781
Young girl

10:20.790 --> 10:22.997
Violence

10:23.000 --> 10:25.070
Center of her own attention

10:25.080 --> 10:26.786
Dex.

10:26.790 --> 10:28.951
That's twice as much
detergent as you need,

10:28.960 --> 10:30.109
maybe three times.

10:30.120 --> 10:32.031
Maybe I like
my shirts itchy.

10:32.040 --> 10:33.871
[ Chuckling ]
That's my shirt.

10:33.880 --> 10:35.745
Not anymore.

10:35.750 --> 10:36.819
[ Laughs ]

10:36.830 --> 10:38.115
God, I love you.

10:38.120 --> 10:42.910
The shades go down,
it's in her head

10:42.920 --> 10:44.740
Painted room

10:44.750 --> 10:46.240
I'm not taking it back.

10:46.250 --> 10:50.368
Can't deny
there's something wrong

10:50.380 --> 10:51.574
Don't call me

10:51.580 --> 10:53.036
Grey: Dex.

10:53.040 --> 10:54.325
Not fit to

10:54.330 --> 10:56.036
Took your advice,
and I called him.

10:56.040 --> 10:57.871
Your dad?

10:57.880 --> 10:59.029
Yeah.
How'd it go?

10:59.040 --> 11:00.701
Well,
I'm still day-drinking.

11:00.710 --> 11:02.450
But he said he'd come here
tonight at 9:00,

11:02.460 --> 11:03.370
so we'll see
what happens.

11:03.380 --> 11:04.870
Well, that's good.

11:04.880 --> 11:05.949
Maybe he'll surprise you.

11:05.960 --> 11:08.201
Yeah. Maybe.

11:08.210 --> 11:10.166
What happened
over at, uh, Hood River?

11:10.170 --> 11:12.286
Um...wel|,
it was pretty rough,

11:12.290 --> 11:13.826
but I think I got
something to go on.

11:13.830 --> 11:15.070
Good. 'Sup, man?

11:16.670 --> 11:18.285
Alright.
I'll leave you two alone.

11:18.290 --> 11:20.167
What's up?
Thanks for coming down.

11:20.170 --> 11:23.879
Um...so, I've been looking at
this guy -- Thomas Junes.

11:23.880 --> 11:25.495
He does three tours,

11:25.500 --> 11:28.572
and then he comes back
and he -- he buys this.

11:28.580 --> 11:30.662
I talked to the Realtor,
and she said he paid cash.

11:30.670 --> 11:31.534
800 grand.

11:31.540 --> 11:33.371
Rich dad?
No.

11:33.380 --> 11:35.075
No, Dad was
a construction worker.

11:35.080 --> 11:36.456
Mother was
a third-grade teacher.

11:36.460 --> 11:38.746
He claims that his wife
is the breadwinner,

11:38.750 --> 11:40.536
but she's
a non-proï¬t lawyer.

11:40.540 --> 11:42.451
I know that he's lying.
He's not talking to me.

11:42.460 --> 11:44.496
So, I was hoping

11:44.500 --> 11:46.786
that maybe you could
put some pressure on him.

11:46.790 --> 11:48.530
Start a case,
look into his financials,

11:48.540 --> 11:50.076
anything to get him to --
to talk to me.

11:50.080 --> 11:51.911
Yeah,
I don't do financials.

11:51.920 --> 11:53.205
That's White Collar.
It's not my division.

11:53.210 --> 11:54.495
Okay, but please?

11:54.500 --> 11:58.823
I will never ask you
for anything again.

11:58.830 --> 12:00.616
Okay, that's not true.
I think we both know that.

12:00.620 --> 12:04.408
But this isn't --
this isn't for a client.

12:06.920 --> 12:08.990
Not fit to be

